post_cb({"bq_ids": {"n4140": {"so_13900421_13900462_0": {"length": 19, "quality": 1.0, "section_id": 5851}}, "n3337": {"so_13900421_13900462_0": {"length": 19, "quality": 1.0, "section_id": 5621}}, "n4659": {"so_13900421_13900462_0": {"length": 15, "quality": 0.7894736842105263, "section_id": 7330}}}, "13900462": {"Id": "13900462", "PostTypeId": "2", "Body": "<p>From the definition of standard layout classes (\u00a79 Classes, paragraph 7)</p>\n<blockquote>\n<p id=\"so_13900421_13900462_0\">[...]<br>\n  * either has no non-static data members in the most derived class and at most one base class with non-static data members, or has no base classes with non-static data members, and<br>\n  [...]</br></br></p>\n</blockquote>\n<p>Both the most-derived class and its base have non-static data members in your case. So it's not standard layout.</p>\n", "LastActivityDate": "2012-12-16T10:39:33.823", "CommentCount": "4", "CreationDate": "2012-12-16T10:39:33.823", "ParentId": "13900421", "Score": "7", "OwnerUserId": "635608"}, "13900421": {"ViewCount": "115", "Body": "<p>A piece of code is worth a thousands words.</p>\n<pre><code>#include &lt;iostream&gt;\n#include &lt;type_traits&gt;\n\nusing namespace std;\n\nstruct A\n{\n    int a;\n};\n\nstruct B : A\n{\n    int b;\n};\n\nint main()\n{\n    cout &lt;&lt; is_standard_layout&lt;B&gt;::value &lt;&lt; endl; // output false! WHY?\n    return 0; \n}\n</code></pre>\n", "AcceptedAnswerId": "13900462", "Title": "Why is this struct not standard-layout?", "CreationDate": "2012-12-16T10:32:40.847", "Id": "13900421", "CommentCount": "0", "PostTypeId": "1", "LastActivityDate": "2012-12-16T10:39:33.823", "Score": "4", "OwnerUserId": "508343", "Tags": "<c++><c++11><struct><typetraits><standard-layout>", "AnswerCount": "1"}});